video.title: The Big Family Cooking Showdown
video.synopsis: In this unscripted series, families passionate about food serve up their most delicious dishes for the chance to be crowned Britain's best home cooks.

episodes.synopsis: The Charles and Marks families face off in three rounds of cooking, preparing Swedish meatballs, spatchcocked chicken, fish soup and more.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: The Karim and Dawes families wow the judges with a spinach and lamb curry, braised pork belly and other mouthwatering foods.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: The Hilliards and Pigotts serve up a mix of successes and failures, from a delectable dry-spiced venison loin to an overseasoned vegetable chili.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: It's an ambitious battle of Indian and Italian flavors -- with a few surprises thrown in -- when the Gangotras take on the Massaccesis.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Deceptively simple Syrian dips and stews from the Ayoubi family stand in stark contrast to the Herberts' fondness for more experimental fare.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: The judges weigh the merits of the Kings' favorite family meals against the Codougans' Caribbean-inspired delicacies -- including curried goat.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: The Bellamores' hearty helpings go up against the Bellamys' Persian heritage, with dueling dishes like salt-baked sea bass and crusted crown of lamb.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: The Boyes and Rignall families put their best dishes forward, from banana and passion fruit soufflés to a cardamom and rose syrup cheesecake.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: Three families return to the Kent countryside to test their skills in the semifinals -- but only one will cook well enough to move on to the final.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: Three more families go head-to-head in a second round of semifinals, stretching their skills in improvisation and sticking to a recipe.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: The last round of semifinals brings the remaining three families to the barn, where they're pressured to cook up winning dishes on the spot.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: With everything on the line, the Top 3 families face the final challenge: preparing a multicourse feast for eight in under five hours.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: Four families hungry to win take on a £10 brunch challenge with surprise ingredients before serving up a fresh pasta bake.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: One family member steps forward to bake a salted caramel chocolate tart. Then it's a team effort to make a two-course meal with oats and beetroot.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: After cooking a £10 meal using frozen ingredients, four new families put a fresh spin on a British classic: fish and chips.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: An individual challenge to make lemon meringue pie tests the contestants' pastry skills. Later on, they cook a two-course meal with lamb and almonds.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: The four families who survived earlier heats go head to head on a pick 'n' mix challenge with celeriac before making an indulgent treat-night meal.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Four new families hit the kitchen for a £10 comfort-food challenge before moving on to make breakfast with a tasty twist.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: One member from each family steps forward to make a savory chicken Kiev. Then the clans reunite to cook goat cheese and passion fruit.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: The judges welcome four new families and ask them to make a one-pot wonder for just 10 quid, then serve up their take on traditional fish cakes.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: One lucky cook from each family must bake a shepherd's pie before joining their clan to make a multicourse meal with smoked haddock and chocolate.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: The four best families from earlier rounds face off in a duck-themed pick 'n' mix, then pull out all the stops to craft a glorious treat-night feast.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: After a series of fiery heats, just four of the 16 families remain. To advance, they must re-create a fish stew and make the most of a whole salmon.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: The three surviving families move forward to finals week where a series of cooking challenges set by Tommy and Angellica await.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: Two families fight to secure the last spot in the finals with a French trimmed "roast in a rush" and a colorful cake for a children's birthday bash.
episodes.title: Episode 13

episodes.synopsis: The final two families face off in a high-stakes showdown, creating a three-course extravaganza with big flavors that are worthy of a win.
episodes.title: Episode 14
